content.detailedDescription: Sitting outside on porch. looked up and saw blinking light .I thought i saw it moving was not sure but use telephone pole and wires to use as a guide to make sure i was seeing it move. i was not afraid. in fact i was talking to it to come closer so i could see it better.It moved down and then going left and out of sight. very slowly. about 7:45 to 9:00 or so. i am still going outside and still see it. maybe noting  not sure what it could be.
content.summary: Moves in same pattern every night

content.detailedDescription:
This description was given to me by someone i know. they have a video.
standing facing south in front of their home approximately 200 ft from highway at 12:13--shortly after midnight, a strange steady orange light was observed south south west approximately a mile from home. it was a clear night, no clouds were observed and very quiet. no traffic passing on road and no wildlife sound. the witness observed the light for about 5 minutes. the light appeared to hover over buildings located in that area. it appeared to be un-moving. in the video the light appeared to be a large object. how large was difficult to ascertain. the light can be seen above the tree line and was a steady non-blinking light. at one point, the witness pointed a high powered blinking flashlight in the direction of the object due being unsure what the light was. the witness was able to see some reflection of a dark shape around the light. right after shining the flashlight at the object, all electricity went out in the neighborhood. this scared the witness who ran inside the home to check on the people inside. all were ok. the electricity came back on, so the witness went back outside and noted that the strange light was gone and an alarm was sounding from the building the light had been hovering over. at this point, the sounds of wildlife returned...Frogs, circadas, and coyotes. approximately an hour later, the witness noted the same orange light north of him and much further away. the light appeared to be moving slowly away from the witness's location and then disappeared

the witness spoke to the people who worked in the building the next morning to see if maybe there was a break-in the night before. they agreed that the alarm had gone off, but there was no sign of a break-in. also spoke to a neighbor who also noted the electricity had gone off for a few seconds the night before.
content.summary: Steady light over tree top

content.detailedDescription:
Just laid down in bed looking out my window to the north,saw what looked like a shooting star, fast through the overcast skies, without the star.It was more like a shadow from the moon. didn't think anything of it, just weird. 10 min. later a bright star like object caught my attention in the northern sky. growing brighter as it came down towards my direction (sse) and wobbled about, very shakey. changed direction to the ne and faded out of range and disappeared. duration from the time  i noticed it to fade out was approximently 3-4 min. time check was 11:09 pm.
no other stars were visible at that time because of the overcast sky. the object didn't just disappear behind a cloud, it faded out because it was traveling away from me out of range and gone.
thinking about what it wasn't....Wasn't a plane, helicopter, or balloon. was not a fireball, star, or falling meteor or the iss or satellite.
putting the shooting star shadow + brighting star like light + the change of directional path = i saw a ufo!!  very cool.
content.summary: Overcast skies, 1st quarter moon to my west, looking north. brighting star-like object decending towards me,turned went ne out of range.

content.altitude: 500 Feet or Less, Over 500 Feet (under cloudcover), Over 500 Feet (no cloudcover)
content.detailedDescription:
On thursday april 27, 2017 at approximately 7:30 pm in west kelowna, british columbia, i was travelling home with my 3 daughters. my 6 year old daughter said “daddy, what are those flashing lights in the sky?” i was travelling in the southwest direction and i looked up to my left and i noticed several (approximatley 6) flashing lights up in the sky that appeared to flashing and what i would describe as dancing in the sky. at first i wasn't sure what to make of them. i thought they were some sort of flares or even military aircraft doing some sort of exercise. but since i live in the okanagan valley and there is no air force bases in the area, i knew they were not any of conventional military aircraft. the objects that i was observing were absolutely silent. given the way these object were moving in the sky, i then realized that what i was witnessing was not a normal or easily explainable occurrence and was most likely extra terrestrial in nature. 

i quickly pulled off to the side of the road and grabbed my phoned got out of my vehicle to start video recording the lights. thats when i noticed a second group of (approximatley 4 or 5) that suddenly appeared below the first group. they looked like they were flying closer to okanagan lake before the flew upward to join the first group. the two groups formed two separate formations and proceeded to fly eastward towards kelowna. i had my camera zoomed in and locked on both groups and continued to record them as they were flying away. or so i thought. after approximately 20-30 seconds of “recording”, i realized that i didn’t actually hit the record button on my phone. i quickly hit the record button and was able to zoom in on the luminous objects as they were flying away. i was able to record the lights, (which were flying in two groups, one approximately 6, the other approximately 4) for about 30 seconds until they essentially were out of sight. 

important points:

although it was early evening and the sun was starting to set, there was still plenty of daylight outside. these objects were extremely bright in sky. i am absolutely certain they were neither airplanes of any type or birds.
the objects appeared to be well below the clouds when i first noticed them as well as below the tops of the mountains. the second group of lights appeared tore flying lower in the valley near the lake
although it did not occur to me at first but what i witnessed i would describe as orange glowing orbs since i did not observe any sort of metallic craft with any visible lines. only lights
the objects that i observed were absolutely silent.
content.summary: Several flashing orbs

content.detailedDescription:
I just got home (at night) and i looked up at the sky. when i noticed the object, i was surprised.   the object was an oval-triangular object.  the object was moving west to east. when it got over my house, it hovered for a while. i looked at it, for a long time.  after a minute (or two), i went inside. when i got inside, i looked outside and it vanished.   
 i was a little surprised,but it didn't really scare me. ever since it happened, i was trying to figure out what it was. i couldn't figure it out and it looked like an ufo , that i saw before (i forget where).  


the object was triangular-oval .  it was more triangle than oval
content.summary: Strange object that's gray, going very slow and it had a weird design

content.detailedDescription:
I was at home with my mom and my infant when i received a telephone call from my sister saying she and my brother-in-law can see a ufo from their apartment and it appears to be closer to my house.  she said i could probably see it from my front yard, but when i went outside and looked, i couldn't see anything in the sky.  i rushed over to their apartment and saw it from their front door area.  it appeared to be a bright light in the sky to the west of bakersfield, ca.  it was very bright and was larger than a star or planet.  as i was watching it, i noticed it would become very bright for a minute or two, and then would quickly dim the lights and then completely turn them off.  

as we all watch this, my sister and brother-in-law said when they noticed it, it was changing colors; however, i didn't notice any other colors than white at that time.  we watched it there for about ten minutes, thinking it would quickly go away, but it didn't.  we then decided to get in the car and see if we could get a closer look.  it took at least 30 minutes to get out to where it was, which was just west of bakersfield and east of the i-5 freeway nearest to snow rd.  

whenever i would start to get close to it, it would turn it's lights off for a minute or two and then reappear a couple miles west.  it did this about another five times before it completely disappeared for good that night.  it should be noted, every time i got closer to it, i began to have the feeling of fear and dread.  

later on that night, the news put a picture up and did a story about it since they received so many calls about it.  they also covered it the next night too since it was seen that night as well.  i took a picture and video of it, but because it was just on my iphone, it doesn't appear as big as it was.  also, the news reports are on youtube.
content.summary: Star-like ufo that would turn off it's lights completelely and then turn them back on and show itself further out.
content.locationName: I-5 freeway and Snow Rd., California

content.detailedDescription: I was gazing up at the stars above me in ahwahnee, california, while on an anniversary trip to the yosemite area.  i could also see a lightning storm that was over the bass lake area.  a large part of the sky above me was clear at the time.  all of a sudden, i had a feeling i needed to look to the west and knew what i would see ahead of time.  when i looked, i saw what appeared to be a satellite-like object that was very high up in the sky, but it was flying much too fast to be a satellite, airplane, helicopter, or drone.  this thing had to be going thousands of miles an hour at least.  also, it didn't have the red or orange tinge like a satellite.  it was bright white like a very bright planet.  i watched this thing come from the west and then make an abrupt 90 degree turn as it just passed me toward southbound without slowing down or banking.  at the speed it was going when it made the sharp turn, i thought it would be impossible for a pilot to do such a maneuver while encountering the g-force of it.  the hole event happened within maybe five seconds at most due to the speed it was going and it quickly went out of my frame of view.  i thought it was interesting to see this, but it made me want answers to so many questions.  it also concerned me that i had some connection to the pilot inside of it and i'm not sure why that was.
content.summary: Star or satilite-like ufo going at an amazing speed and making a 90 degree turn without slowing or banking

content.detailedDescription: Around 9:36 my husband and i muted the tv as we heard what sounded like a very loud helicopter right above our house, but it sounded off like a propeller was missing. i grabbed my phone and we ran out back and looked around as the noise was fading like it was powering down, as i got to the opening of the trees there were 3 lights blinking on and off in a straight line then other lights would blink the same way above and below and each side of the first set of 3 lights. this lasted for about 20 seconds, then they stopped. they were right above the power line tower in our back yard, so close to the tree top and in a very large area, i'd say about the size of a house about 500 ft above us. we then felt like we should get inside, this was a frightening situation as it was real and so close to us. i did record it but being night time, i only got a quick shot of the lights. also on a quick note, the day before today, i saw a large thick white object hovering higher up towards the north moving slowly east,it was pure white and i wouldn't have noticed it if i wasn't showing my grandson an airplane that flew past it and my 2 year old grandson thought it was a star, but this was at 3pm and a clear sky.
content.summary: Loud unusual noise, then about 5 flashing bright lights above back yard in a straight line then above and below the straight line

content.detailedDescription:

i have been around airplanes my whole life and have never seen anything like this. the event was over nas fallon in northern nevada. might have been an f-22 or f-35 showing of for the navy.
i never saw what kind of craft was leaving the contrail, couldn't even see a speck.
nas fallon is 25 to 30 miles from my property.
content.summary: Contrail with 90 degree turn

content.detailedDescription:
I was outside my home, as i don't sleep well and often go out to star gaze. standing in my driveway facing west at 3 am 5-2-2017 and off my left side vision looking up at approximately a 15% from vertical i noticed movement and looked directly at the objects. they were dimly lit light tan in color moving with no sound from my left to my right. event only lasted about 6/7 seconds before they were out of view to the north east. i noticed as they passed over head they reminded me of a football team, front line and then line backer line, with movement and changing positions but always moving in unison as a group. i figured the altitude of them was about 1000 foot. the size of each of the round lit tan orbs was about the size of a dime or penny.

i have had many sightings here in this town as have a number of my friends here also, but this was the closest event for me. 

there didn't seem to be one structure that they were all part of but just a group of them all moving together. 

then the next night, 5-3-17 at about the same time 3 am, i was up and decided to go out to see if there might be any again? i was in the same location on my driveway facing west looking at about the same angle on the east side of my house. watched for about 3-4 minutes, nothing, so i moved around to the back side, west side of my house to have a further view west to watch for a few minutes. within just a moment i seen three groups of them coming from the sw heading in the same direction as the night before and about the same altitude, but not moving as fast. each of the three lines of groups had 6-10 dimly lit light tan orbs moving and acting the same as the night before. this night i had my very bright flash light with me and shown it right at them but there was to reflection or change in their path. then about 3 or 4 seconds another object following the same path and at the same altitude came into view but it was definitely a triangle with just 3 lite tan orbs, one of each corner. solid body this one was and i shined my light on it and could see it was solid, and as it passed overhead it would block out the stars behind. it appeared to be about 8 to 10 foot on each side of the craft. the surface of it appeared to be a dull gray with no reflection from my light, and it did not react to my light either.

this sighting lasted just a few seconds also as they all passed to the nne and out of my sight. pretty exciting. my cell phone camera could not detect them as they were not bright enough. i am going to be out there again tonight with a digital camera that might pick them up of there is another event. seems odd that both sightings were following the same path and at about the same altitude, with just a slight speed difference.

i have had a number of sighting while living in this town over the last 17+ years, as have many others here.
content.summary: Group of 10 moving sw to ne no sound approx. 1000 ft altitude.

content.detailedDescription: Driving to work overcast no visible lights in sky until i noticed a very bright solid orange light in the sky traveling from southeast to northern direction at first thought was a airplane but strange looking so i pulled over to observe it the object stopped and hovered took 2 pictures and went to work while driving notice the object was moving as well got to work got out to look for this object at first nothing but then appeared above i asked a coworker to look at the object with me during this time the object dimmed out completely thought it was gone but then it brightened back up very bright the object did this 3 times i had to go in work came back outside a 1 and half hour later the sun was up and the object was very high up and was reflecting the sun off of it. at this time as well 3 jets were now in the sky approximately 3 to 5 minutes after the jets appeared the just vanished my coworker also observed this.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Observed very bright orange light moving from southeast to northern object stopped and hovered for 3min and moved northern direction and stopped and hovered for 1 hrs and half and finally ascended up and disappeared

content.detailedDescription: Got home from work around 02:20 - 30 just happ ned to look up in the south direction and noticed a flashing light with colors.  it was dancing around and then i got my phone and started to record it, it was a little windy and i was trying to focus it in.  i watched it for a minute and 30 seconds.  there were no planes or helicopters around and i did look for them and at the angle that i saw it at in the sky there was no way it could have been a reflection from anything where i was at. the recording is a little shaky and it might need to be stabilized.
content.summary: Flashing different colors, bouncing around.

content.detailedDescription:
It was around 11pm & i was standing on my roof overlooking san francisco. 

i was looking at stars & jupiter to the south when i spotted 3 dark grey circles (less dark than rest of sky) arranged in an equilateral triangle travelling silently at high speeds from the w/sw and towards the ne. although these lights were already travelling rapidly, they accelerated upwards and to the ne rapidly with no sound.

since i live near sfo & oak flight paths, commercial airliners were also visible in the sky at the same time. three things stood out that made this sighting significantly different than any other plane/craft i've ever seen in the sky before: (1) rapid speed & incredible acceleration, (2) absolutely soundless/silent operation (2) no illumination or lights on the craft. 

this object flew & accelerated rapidly upwards & disappeared out of sight towards the ne (over downtown san francisco or perhaps already over the bay... the 3 dark grey circles became too far away too see - it was dark outside & the object was not illuminated by any lights).

based on my google & youtube searches for similar sightings, i believe i possibly could have seen the underside of a b2 stealth bomber as it flew back over sf from a flight over the pacific.
content.summary: Very dark out at night. 3 dark grey circles (less dark than rest of sky) travelling silently at high speeds to the ne. accelerated upwards and to the ne rapidly with no sound.

content.detailedDescription:
Bedford-stuyvesant.
a helicopter was circling the area that looked to be police or news channel operated. i looked up to notice a flying object with three points changing shape and moving across the sky. i ran to grab binoculars to watch the object. it continued to move and glow and change shape and then the object seems to separate and fall in pieces. another helicopter immediately joined, circling the area. then another... they're hovering now, but the object(s) is gone from sight. i think they may be news helicopters that have nothing to do with what i saw. it was the circling helicopters that caused me to look up and see the strange object.
content.summary: Object changing shape with three points. circling helicopter present before. another helicopter joined after.

content.detailedDescription: March 3 2016 went to hike at alta ski resort with wife. knew that a incoming storm was coming. after returning to our car in the parking area. sky was covered in storm clouds high winds and snow started. a break appeared in clouds with the sun appearing in the edge. i saw a staionary brilliant blue image (blur) in the middle of the storm cloud deck. brought this to my partners attention. took out my cell phone (galaxy s6) to capture it thinking it was a sundog reflection on clouds. shot the picture through the sunroof enlarged it and saw the blur was two orbs with similar lighter apendages. steped out of the car to look to see if it was due to the polerized sunroof,it was not. it was still visible to the naked eye. the objects seem to have caused a shadow image in the sky some distance between itself and the canera. the orbs remained visible for about 45 minutes till the gap in the clouds covered it completely. i am a avid skywatcher amature astronomer. i have seen many sky phenomenon of sun/sky and clouds. this was different from any i have observed in the past. the storm front was moving from west to east with wind gust to 50 mph a ground level these objects seemed unaffected by the storm and were staionary even thogh the wind was likely much greater at the altitude it was observed at. i showed the image's to my son on our return home. he urged me to send them to mufon then and has kept after till he sat me down to send them to you now.
content.summary: Severe storm event cloud break around the sun. noticed bright blue blur. took pictue from car, enlarged shot to find blur was two orbs  reshot siting out of car .

content.detailedDescription:
A very large size, gray color object hover without any noice over brooklyn. i personally don't know what it could be. i had a good 15 minutes sharp view of the object. i was trying to be rational but find no answer. unfortunately the video footage doesn't give back the ratio of the object. much larger than a boeing ch-47 chinook helicopter. i have photos captured also and after zooming i saw the object have colors and lights. 
date 03-05-17 brooklyn 8am
content.summary: A large size , gray color , square shape ufo hover over brooklyn

content.detailedDescription:
We were traveling southbound on i-5 from medford, or. it was around 2am. i was the passenger and my girlfriend was the driver.
we took an exit soon after hitting the mountains towards the border (we think it was exit 6) to take a break.
we remember it was clear and still upon pulling off the freeway and shutting down the car. we cracked both windows.
w remember a large wind gush for a short period from east to west, which then stopped completely. thinking back on it, it was very unusual to weather conditions at the time. possibly ufo arriving.
looking straight ahead above the tree line in front of us at the stars, we notice a blue pulsing orb slightly larger than most stars, just above the treeline. at first we thought it was a planet.
we both simultaneously got a gut feeling of extreme discomfort. we realized it was not a planet, but was positioning itself in a way to appear as one. it had a distinctive hypnotizing effect with its blue light/glow (darker blue to lighter/almost white then back, varying shades and intensities and patterns, very hard not to look at). felt as if it was fairly close, perhaps ~100m. it is hard to be sure, as it felt camouflaged or cloaked to some extent.
as soon as we noticed it and became vocal to one another about it, it may have slightly moved before it vanished for perhaps 1 minute and then reappeared in almost the exact same spot. it disappeared again a moment later, and we made the decision to leave quickly.
we got back onto the freeway, continuing southbound on i-5. as we left we looked back and could not locate the ufo. there were a couple vehicles as we re-entered the freeway, but they ended up out of our vision shorty after.
we continued to drive, thinking it was gone. there where no vehicles on the interstate in either direction during the encounters both when we where sitting still and driving.
then 2-3 minutes later, my girlfriend saw it reappear above and in front of and to the right of the car. it seemed to be matching our speed and course precisely.
it felt larger than it looked, and it had a significant effect on us psychologically. it did not feel "right".
as my girlfriend was pointing out the object, several odd events occurred.
my girlfriend describes getting a sort of tunnel vision, in which she became so fixated on the object as she drove, that she felt as if the rest of her vision was filling in with (black)static, around the object (leaving only the object in her center vision).
because of the reaction of my girlfriend, instead of looking at the object, i looked at her in the drivers seat.
at that moment it was as if all the lights went out momentarily and everything was pitch black. as i was looking at her, it felt as if everything "turned off", and in that sense i mean my own cognitive processes (sight, sound, feeling etc.) as well as electronic and mechanical. my girlfriend experienced this is the sense that everything disappeared momentarily from her mind except for the object and she felt as if she was being hypnotized. for me it felt like i was numbed completely for a moment and lost all sense of input and it felt as if i was alone in the car, quiet and still but observed. my girlfriend also felt this feeling of being alone in the car suddenly, an uncomfortable void of one sided observation.
neither of us feel we were abducted, it felt more like we were scanned in some way and it was so powerful (or intentionally designed) it overloaded our mind and all of the electronics and car momentarily.
my girlfriend remembers simply not being able to look away, and being worried about crashing the car due to her inability to focus on the road/fading concentration. something like an insect attracted to light.
after this moment it disappeared as we both began to exchange animated words. at this point we attempted to find another vehicle. we found a truck and followed it. it never reappeared. we tagged along with other vehicles for the rest of the i-5 mountain range because it seemed to want to isolate us from its behavoir.
our observations and intuition make us believe it was likely no larger than 3m although it did seem to mask itself and undesired of being observed.
it felt cold, calculated, robotic, methodical, curious.
content.summary: Blue orb floating, followed us for short period, short unexplainable "blackout"

content.detailedDescription: I was at the restaurant and i was lookin out the window and i saw the big ufo flying across the sky. it had a big green critter in it. i was so scared i was literally shaking and i called a ufo investigator to go kil it. i also shot it with my 2nd amendment and it killed my friend john. rip john.

content.detailedDescription: So cal in the san fernando valley. woke up about 3am was staring out window into clear night sky looking at the stars when a fast flying object flew rather quickly by it had lights surrounded it flashing. it didn't look like anything i ever seen before. elongated shape maybe....It was flashing lights...Was flying at a rate of high speed travelling south west in the sky. it happened rather quickly

content.detailedDescription: I was looking at the moon with my telescope when it slowly went by the moon. i took a picture when i saw it. when it was past the moon the circular object couldn't be seen and  no light beams. i was only trying to observe a meteor/meteors. when i could'nt locate it i switched my focus to the moon. i was maybe observing the moon for 20min before it came across. it was hardly visible by eye sight.
content.summary: I was looking at the moon with my telescope when it slowly went by the moon

content.detailedDescription: My girlfriend and i were on our way home and driving on highway 50- east in placerville (where we both live). we were approaching the part of the highway where the speed limit changes to 40 mph because you are going through downtown. we both noticed a light in the distance behind the trees on our left. it was just one dot of orange light that would get brighter and then fade and turn slightly yellow looking. it was around 1:15 am on april 26, 2017, so there was no one else on the road. i slowed down to about 25 mph to try and get enough time to see it before it disappeared behind the trees. after watching this object for about a minute we went around a corner and lost sight of it. when we came all the way around the corner the object moved away from the trees and began to move across the highway towards the parking garage. we noticed that it now looked like three bright orangeish yellow lights, and was clearly some sort of object. the placement of the lights made me think it was triangular in shape. it was not an airplane because it's lights were very large, and not flashing. i also rolled down my window, and even though the object was no more than 200 feet away from our car- there was no sound at all. i turned into the parking garage and raced to the top floor to try and get a good view of it, but by the time we got to the top this object was gone. it must have been able to accelerate at an incredible speed to be completely gone from sight in the 60 seconds or so it took me to get to the third floor of the parking garage. i also feel that it wasn't some kind of drone or toy, because i could tell that it was at least 15 feet wide (based on surrounding objects). my conclusion is that it wasn't any kind of conventional aircraft, like a plane. i've lived near the placerville airport for the past couple years and can easily spot what plane lights look like. this object was not a plane.
content.summary: I was driving east on hwy 50 and noticed a pulsating light behind the trees that eventually moved directly over the highway and then disappeared. it was 1:15 am and it was me and one other person in the car who saw it.

content.detailedDescription:
We have had heavy rains/cloud cover for several days. i work nights, so i let our two dogs out before retiring.  tonight is cloud free and the big dipper was bright.  i thought it unusual that even at about 2:00 am there were no planes in the sky.  

i did not bring my iphone with me.  i do use the plane finder app (i paid for it) and the noaa weather app.  after what i saw i checked both and there was no indication of cloud cover near us and no plans were headed in a southeastern direction.  as a matter of fact, the nearest plane would have been a few miles to our north.

i noticed the object headed at a consistent rate of speed but not more than 200 mph in a southeasterly direction at what i would guess was about 20000-25000 feet.  it's not what i would consider a normal flight path for planes in this area.  

it appeared to have a greenish light that slowly blinked while a bluish-white light remained steady.  i mentioned to myself that i finally saw a plane tonight, and at that moment it abruptly disappeared.  i waited about three to five minutes more to see if it appeared anywhere else along or outside its trajectory.  i thought it perhaps had run into clouds.  there was no sound.

it was at this point that i took the dogs inside and checked my phone for clouds or planes.
content.summary: Lone object in sky disappeared

content.detailedDescription:
Was looking up to the sky, 12:25 am. about a minute ago actually . i just happened to be looking up at the sky while bbqing (late time to bbq i know lol) & i was looking at what i think was a satellite, then suddenly an object that was lower than the satellite and possibly higher than an airplane, starting flying quickly but steadily glided, it looked like a llowly lit orb type  object that wouldn't have been visible unless you were focused on the sky like i was. 
it was so dim it probably wouldn't have been noticeable looking out of a window. it was dimmer than a star and almost blended into the sky but was clearly a sphere.
from where i was it was pretty small but it looked like it would have been quite large or  medium size judging on the altitude and size from where i could see it .. it was completely silent. gliding in an unnaturally straight line then dissapeared from my view within seconds. literally took about 5 seconds to travel across the whole sky (from my point of view which is still incredible, because it would take a normal aircraft about 1-2 minutes longer to travel the distance ). it had no trail,  my mom and i both saw it and believe it was too faint to be a meteorite, too slow to be a shooting star  and it was impossible to be any aircraft i know of as it had no lights or sound, and it glided in such an odd way, and was almost fluttering even tho it had zero lights on it, it looked like an orb with some sort of cloaking device if i could describe it best. . very strange. 
i've seen lights i couldn't identify in the sky before and humored that it could have been a ufo. but this one made me feel different. it was clearly an object with mass. and if not a ufo possibly a big and close asteroid, which i doubt because it would have been noticed by professionals  i'd hope lol.
content.summary: Quick, silent & lightless orb un-naturally crosses sky in 5-7 seconds

content.detailedDescription: Looking out our high rise window at lake michigan.   the pulsating and brightness of the object and how it just appeared out of nowhere.  i thought the object was venus.  the object was clearly moving in a ladder formation this was observable for a long period of time by both of us.  i was dumbfounded when my girlfriend pointed out that the object was moving.  the object finally went behind another building and we could no longer see it.
content.summary: We are in a high rise next to lake michigan told my girlfriend it was venus but then the object started ascending in a ladder pattern

content.detailedDescription: A friend and i were way out in the country on a lake, clear night at the end of may, 2009.  we were star gazing, and my friend had his tripod set up.  we suddenly saw a moving large star like ufo.  extremely high altitude, and it moved at a semi fast rate, then turned and went away from view.  it was not a satellite, as i've seen them slowly move through the sky before.  it was very startling to both of us and my friend took a great picture, leaving his exposure open to see the path of the ufo.
content.summary: A friend and i were way out in the country on a lake, clear night at the end of may, 2009.  we were star gazing, and my friend had his tripod set up.  we suddenly saw a moving large star like ufo.

content.detailedDescription: Was looking out window about 9pm, then suddenly a star sized light just seemed to appear in the sw sky. something didn't look right. seemed like it was flickering. asked wife, and she confirmed. looked at it thru my binaculars. wow! green,red,blue sort of orb kinda dancing around, then suddenly it would spin in a circle.(kind of like watching someone whip around a glow stick in the dark). seemed to change shape alot. crazy!! slowly drifted off to the west over a course of about a half hour.
content.summary: Reflective, light changing star sized orb, would at times spin in circles. slowly moved t west.

content.detailedDescription: I was visiting the chapel in sedona with my mother & sister and took several photos of both the chapel and the various views around. it was only after i returned home and viewed the photos on my home computer's 27 inch monitor that i notice in one of the frames that i was taking consecutive photos of my mother & sister that i notice an "object" in the background above the mountains in the sky. this object is only visible in the one frame and is not shown in the frame before and after in the series of photos that i had taken that afternoon. i did not witness anything in the sky with my naked eye nor do i think anyone else noticed anything as well.
content.summary: I did not witness it, but caught it on camera as i was taking several (8) photos in a row, the object was captured on one frame and none others
